	<key>readme</key>
	<string>Google Tasks workflow for Alfred. Manage your tasks without leaving Alfred.

SETUP
  1. Create a Google Cloud project and enable the Tasks API
  2. Create a Desktop OAuth client and download client_secret.json
  3. Place client_secret.json in the workflow data directory:
     ~/Library/Application Support/Alfred/Workflow Data/com.rhuss.gtasks/
  4. Type "gt login" to authenticate

See the README for detailed setup instructions:
https://github.com/rhuss/alfred-google-tasks-workflow

COMMANDS
  gt login                          Authenticate with Google
  gt add &lt;task&gt;                     Create a task
  gt add &lt;task&gt;, tomorrow           Create with a due date
  gt add &lt;task&gt;, friday #Shopping   Create in a specific list
  gt list                           Show tasks by timeframe
  gt list #Work                     Show tasks from one list
  gt open                           Open Google Tasks in browser
  gt logout                         Disconnect your account

DATES
  today, tomorrow, monday-sunday, next week,
  2026-07-15 (ISO), 07-15 (month-day)

LISTS
  Add #ListName at the end to target a list.
  Lists are created automatically if they don't exist.
  Hyphens/underscores become spaces: #My-List = "My List"</string>
